THE CONVOY

17
00:02:47,210 --> 00:02:49,200
Hey, old man, where you going?

18
00:02:59,890 --> 00:03:02,250
What's the matter?
- What'd you do with it?

19
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:05,290
Hi.
- I said, why throw the bottle?

20
00:03:09,130 --> 00:03:10,690
Why did you smash the bottle?

21
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:24,530
Call the cops!
He'll kill him!

22
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:30,050
Jail, old man. You're gonna get
banged up! Cool down!

23
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:42,890
Tanya!

24
00:03:47,290 --> 00:03:49,120
Tanya!

25
00:03:51,850 --> 00:03:53,000
Tanya!

26
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,570
Does it hurt?

27
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:18,890
Where?
- Here.

28
00:04:19,370 --> 00:04:21,330
No, not here it doesn't.

29
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:25,040
The fainting spells will continue
if you keep ignoring the pain.

30
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:32,040
There's no cure for migraines,
but you do have to control the pain.

31
00:04:34,930 --> 00:04:36,650
Take these with water.

32
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:44,090
If it hits you, take a bath.
Hot water will stop it for a while.

33
00:04:51,970 --> 00:04:54,440
Stop ignoring the pain, Ignat.

34
00:04:54,890 --> 00:04:58,120
You'll start hallucinating.
Seeing things.

35
00:05:03,890 --> 00:05:07,410
If you keep refusing preventive measures,
I'll report you to the regiment.

36
00:05:09,410 --> 00:05:11,320
I won't.

37
00:05:19,330 --> 00:05:22,370
Comrade Captain, those little brats
wrote a complaint to the precinct

38
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:24,880
and attached a doctor's note.

39
00:05:25,570 --> 00:05:28,770
You broke this punk's bone,
and messed up his Adam's apple.

40
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:31,480
The higher-ups are stricter these days.
You know how it is.

41
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,680
Everyone is sick of disorderly conduct.

42
00:05:34,490 --> 00:05:38,530
Were you drunk or something?
- I'm not apologizing.

43
00:05:45,290 --> 00:05:47,970
You're going on detached duty, Ignat,
AWOL retrieval.

44
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:51,720
Two newbies took off,
and stole cash from the office.

45
00:05:53,330 --> 00:05:54,930
The soldiers aren't armed; fuck 'em.

46
00:05:55,010 --> 00:05:57,530
We're not gonna raise hell.
Who needs that?

47
00:05:58,170 --> 00:06:03,010
But it's government money.
We have to get it back.

48
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:07,080
I'm assigning you a contract sergeant.

49
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:08,850
He's waiting for you.

50
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:15,410
Lay low on detached duty, Ignat.
Wait this out and keep your nose clean.

51
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:25,050
Understand about the money?
- Yes, sir.

52
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:27,930
You're going to the AWOL's place of
residence, with a layover in Moscow.

53
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,800
Moscow. Got it.

54
00:06:30,770 --> 00:06:32,450
Don't fuck this up,
Comrade Captain,

55
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:35,330
one more stunt,
and I'll throw the book at you.

56
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:38,090
Guaranteed dishonourable
discharge, maybe even worse.

57
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:39,770
A criminal case.

58
00:06:39,890 --> 00:06:41,530
I'm sick of disorderly conduct.

59
00:06:45,170 --> 00:06:47,480
Permission to speak,
Comrade Captain?

60
00:06:47,730 --> 00:06:50,770
The boys want to know, " Why doesn't
Comrade Captain shave himself?"

61
00:06:50,850 --> 00:06:54,530
They're, like, going on about how
Comrade Captain could cut his throat, like.

62
00:06:54,570 --> 00:06:56,770
"Comrade Captain
can't feel pain".

63
00:06:57,050 --> 00:06:58,960
I think that's bullshit,
Comrade Captain.

64
00:06:59,050 --> 00:07:01,360
I think once you draw blood,
your hand stops by itself.

65
00:07:01,450 --> 00:07:04,450
With a blade, Comrade Captain,
everyone feels pain.

66
00:07:19,690 --> 00:07:21,450
I'm sorry, Comrade Captain.

67
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:44,290
Good day, Comrade Captain.

68
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:54,890
They've found Timofeyev, the first AWOL.
The cops are setting up a local raid.

69
00:07:58,010 --> 00:08:01,610
We should go pick him up,
before it's too late.

70
00:08:14,490 --> 00:08:16,800
Should we take guns, Comrade Captain?

71
00:09:22,410 --> 00:09:23,970
What's going on here?

72
00:09:27,450 --> 00:09:30,490
That's what.
- Whatcha waiting for? Call an ambulance.

73
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:35,160
Stabbed with an awl.
Ran him through, the bastard.

74
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:39,440
The fucker's hiding up there.
- An athlete, eh?

75
00:09:42,530 --> 00:09:44,680
Timofeyev went nuts,
Comrade Captain.

76
00:09:44,850 --> 00:09:47,730
This is a murder; what can we do?
Let the cops deal with it.

77
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:51,400
We could use a sniper.
- Nah, not necessary.

78
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:54,770
Did I get him, Comrade Captain?

79
00:10:54,850 --> 00:10:56,450
With one hit.

80
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:04,200
A steady arm can come in handy.

81
00:11:07,050 --> 00:11:09,770
Don't get me wrong, Comrade Captain,
I'm not a violent man.

82
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:14,610
The cop was a piece of shit.

83
00:11:15,410 --> 00:11:17,640
He wouldn't have lived long anyway.

84
00:11:18,530 --> 00:11:21,970
Didn't even know me
and was mouthing off at me.

85
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:24,090
Started talking about my mother.

86
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:27,730
That scum tried to humiliate me.
I wasn't having that.

87
00:11:29,650 --> 00:11:31,930
You sure he's dead, Comrade Captain?

88
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:39,770
Give me the awl, Timofeyev. If the riot
police find out, they'll take you down.

89
00:11:41,130 --> 00:11:43,970
Think I'm a shit?
- You tell me.

90
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:47,970
I'm not gonna die alone.

91
00:11:48,810 --> 00:11:50,850
You're not gonna kill me.

92
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:53,410
You think it's not in me?

93
00:11:53,690 --> 00:11:58,320
You take me down, who's gonna
protect you from the cops?

94
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:02,330
What, like there are no cops in jail?
- You won't live to see remand.

95
00:12:05,570 --> 00:12:07,170
Fine, here it is then.

96
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:23,290
You stole money. You have to give
it back to the government.

97
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,970
Nineteen thousand.
Spent half of it on grub.

98
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:36,690
Where's your friend?
- He's not my friend. He's a clown.

99
00:12:36,730 --> 00:12:39,200
Why is he a clown?
- Shrieks like a bird.

100
00:12:39,370 --> 00:12:41,090
And where's he shrieking now?

101
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:44,610
No way, Comrade Captain.
You really think I'm a shit.

102
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:48,690
Get in my car now.

103
00:12:51,410 --> 00:12:55,730
I killed a cop. The cops are gonna get me.
In prison, I'm dead either way.

104
00:12:57,410 --> 00:13:00,850
Listen, Captain,
give the money to my mum.

105
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:03,930
So she can pray for my soul.
- It's the government's money.

106
00:13:03,970 --> 00:13:06,970
You stole it.
I have to sign for it.

107
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:11,920
It was a good hit, eh?
- No, it wasn't.

108
00:13:20,450 --> 00:13:22,520
You're all fucked. Bitches.

109
00:13:40,690 --> 00:13:43,450
Turned out to be a smart kid.
Saved everyone a lot of hassle.

110
00:13:43,530 --> 00:13:46,680
Nice one, pal.
You saw the kid alive last?

111
00:13:46,770 --> 00:13:48,370
What can you tell me?
- Nothing.

112
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:50,320
Did he ask you anything?
Hey, bro, did he?

113
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:52,330
I'm not your bro, pig?

114
00:13:52,850 --> 00:13:56,370
What did you say? Hey!
Hey, come back here.

115
00:13:56,410 --> 00:13:59,050
Get off your high horse, Sergeant.
We identified Timofeyev's body.

116
00:13:59,090 --> 00:14:01,130
I'll sign whatever you want.

117
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:04,370
If I find out the soldier
didn't jump, I'll come after you.

118
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:15,200
The boys fight for cash in the barracks,
saving up for demobilization.

119
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:19,290
A hundred to whoever remains standing.
Timofeyev was the biggest thug.

120
00:14:19,370 --> 00:14:22,650
Stomped one of our boys half to death.
Sent him to the hospital, broke his arm.

121
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:25,970
Ruptured his spleen, the bastard.
Timofeyev was asking for it.

122
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:29,370
Don't worry about it, Comrade Captain.
He got what he deserved.

123
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:31,640
You want a reprimand?

124
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:35,400
A reprimand? A reprimand would
fuck up my whole contract.

125
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:37,920
The paymaster would start
getting tight with the money.

126
00:14:39,490 --> 00:14:41,370
No, you don't get it.

127
00:14:41,770 --> 00:14:43,450
Of course I get it.

128
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:47,450
Eyes on the road.

129
00:14:50,730 --> 00:14:52,450
Can I sit here?

130
00:14:53,050 --> 00:14:54,850
Here, the stool is better.

131
00:14:55,570 --> 00:14:58,930
Hand over the deserter.
- We already did that once.

132
00:14:58,970 --> 00:15:02,930
Unauthorized absence from the unit
means up to four years in prison.

133
00:15:02,965 --> 00:15:06,210
Let's make a deal. The commander
will turn a blind eye.

134
00:15:06,290 --> 00:15:09,520
Tugayev will finish his service
and go home.

135
00:15:09,930 --> 00:15:13,530
I was telling Artyom not to enlist.

136
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,810
But he did anyway.

137
00:15:24,210 --> 00:15:29,575
You got it into his head, fuckwit.
"A boy has a duty..."

138
00:15:29,610 --> 00:15:34,400
Kept saying, "You'll come back a man".
- It was Artyom's decision.

139
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:36,650
I told him, " Don't enlist.

140
00:15:36,890 --> 00:15:41,330
It's hell. Don't stick your neck
into the noose".

141
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:45,650
But he did it anyway!
Now look; he's AWOL.

142
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:49,240
He did the right thing
- The right thing?! What right thing?!

143
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:51,280
Artyom made his choice.

144
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:54,370
Why couldn't he choose his mother?

145
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:58,410
Why? I told him,
"Get a doctor's note".

146
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:00,410
Didn't I tell him?

147
00:16:03,290 --> 00:16:07,370
That's right, Captain,
Don't look for my son here.

148
00:16:08,690 --> 00:16:10,130
Come here.

149
00:16:17,530 --> 00:16:22,080
What are you doing?
Don't touch that bed.

150
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:28,440
Just leave my mother alone.

151
00:16:51,570 --> 00:16:56,330
Meat pies?
- With these prices...

152
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:57,770
...be glad to get those.
- It's good.

153
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:00,770
Good thing we're leaving tonight.

154
00:17:00,970 --> 00:17:03,280
You'd spend all the
government's cash on grub.

155
00:17:03,330 --> 00:17:06,640
Forget the pies, Comrade Captain.
We have money.

156
00:17:07,370 --> 00:17:10,090
You know, Timofeyev's money.
It's nobody's money.

157
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:12,650
Don't be afraid of the brass,
Comrade Captain.

158
00:17:12,690 --> 00:17:14,850
They already reported the money
as lost.

159
00:17:14,885 --> 00:17:16,810
They already wrote it off.

160
00:17:17,610 --> 00:17:20,760
We can go out on the town,
burn some cash. Cool, huh?

161
00:17:21,090 --> 00:17:24,610
A whole day in Moscow.
Something to tell the guys about.

162
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:27,130
You can't do Moscow with no money.

163
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:33,170
We could see the city,
Comrade Captain; look around.

164
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:37,640
You like Moscow?
- The city would be mine by nightfall.

165
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:40,930
When your contract's done,
knock yourself out.

166
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:44,480
Here, have a pie.

167
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:44,930
First time in Moscow?

168
00:18:45,210 --> 00:18:48,360
What about you?
- No, not me.

169
00:18:51,490 --> 00:18:52,850
Here.

170
00:18:53,930 --> 00:18:55,650
Nah, that shit does nothing for me.

171
00:18:55,730 --> 00:18:58,530
Moscow is like a whore:
You need a warm-up.

172
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:04,050
Let me go.

173
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,530
No, nothing I can do.

174
00:19:18,890 --> 00:19:22,570
The boss will look the other way,
I know the secret way to ask.

175
00:19:22,610 --> 00:19:24,250
The captain won't go for it.

176
00:19:25,490 --> 00:19:29,120
I can't go back to the barracks.
I'll go crazy.

177
00:19:31,130 --> 00:19:32,890
No, there's nothing I can do.

178
00:19:34,330 --> 00:19:37,410
Think about it, bro:
Once you jump the fence,

179
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,250
you can't go back, it's hell.

180
00:19:39,370 --> 00:19:42,170
Once you've been AWOL,
you're screwed, you know?

181
00:19:42,210 --> 00:19:44,970
Get off my back.
- What did I say?

182
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:47,930
A load of crap. The captain's brutal,
he's facing criminal charges.

183
00:19:47,970 --> 00:19:52,130
Drunk and disorderly?
- Murder, but not proved yet.

184
00:19:53,170 --> 00:19:54,930
Premeditated murder?

185
00:19:55,730 --> 00:19:57,960
The boys say he killed his daughter.

186
00:19:59,850 --> 00:20:02,530
His own daughter?

187
00:20:02,610 --> 00:20:04,440
He'll get you too, bro.

188
00:20:08,010 --> 00:20:10,970
Let me go, bro.
Don't push me. I'll get mad.

189
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:14,210
Go ahead
- Yeah? I could, y'know...

190
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:17,010
Whatever. It's just...
- Just what?

191
00:20:17,130 --> 00:20:20,410
Just, you don't have the balls.
- I can leave.

192
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:22,960
Again, huh?
- What?

193
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:26,770
You're scared again.
- I'm not scared.

194
00:20:35,490 --> 00:20:37,690
Thought I was wasted, right?
Thought I was nice?

195
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:42,640
Lay off, you'll get yourself dirty.
- Thought I'd take pity on you?

196
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:45,440
Don't touch shit, you'll stink.

197
00:20:45,490 --> 00:20:48,690
Jail doesn't do shit for your kind.
People like you should be killed.

198
00:20:50,730 --> 00:20:55,050
I swear, the captain'll turn a blind eye,
I know a secret.

199
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:08,290
Damn Moscow!

200
00:21:08,650 --> 00:21:10,480
It's not working, Comrade Captain?

201
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:12,850
Give me your hands.

202
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:16,090
Take them off.

203
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:20,840
Why, Comrade Captain?
The cops will sniff around.

204
00:21:20,930 --> 00:21:23,530
Down. Pushups.
- What do you mean, down?

205
00:21:24,170 --> 00:21:26,890
You don't get it.
- What, in a public toilet?

206
00:21:26,930 --> 00:21:29,320
You don't get it.
- You mean, hands on the ground?

207
00:21:30,490 --> 00:21:32,170
No, you don't get it.

208
00:21:36,370 --> 00:21:40,410
One, two, three,

209
00:21:40,570 --> 00:21:44,650
four, five, six,

210
00:21:44,850 --> 00:21:49,290
seven, eight, nine,

211
00:21:49,490 --> 00:21:52,090
ten, eleven...

212
00:22:05,410 --> 00:22:07,290
You hurt yourself?
- No, Comrade Captain.

213
00:22:07,370 --> 00:22:10,650
It's the pies. Bad for my stomach.
- Did you know that before?

214
00:22:10,690 --> 00:22:13,000
Yeah.
- Then why'd you stuff your face?

215
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:14,850
It hurts. I need a doctor.

216
00:22:33,490 --> 00:22:35,720
What the hell?
- Good ketchup.

217
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:37,770
You'll have to lick it up.

218
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:39,250
Get up.

219
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:40,730
What's with you?

220
00:22:40,890 --> 00:22:43,170
What about him?
- Eyes front.

221
00:22:44,330 --> 00:22:45,370
What's this?

222
00:22:45,450 --> 00:22:47,520
Ketchup, Comrade Captain.
Disgusting shit.

223
00:22:47,610 --> 00:22:49,730
You're disgusting shit.
Need proof?

224
00:22:50,610 --> 00:22:52,840
Permission to clean myself up,
Comrade Captain?

225
00:22:52,930 --> 00:22:54,450
Forward march.

226
00:23:02,970 --> 00:23:05,440
You got eyes like a bull,
Comrade Captain.

227
00:23:05,930 --> 00:23:07,610
Don't red flies bother you?

228
00:23:07,970 --> 00:23:10,330
Why didn't you tell me
the sergeant attacked you?

229
00:23:10,410 --> 00:23:11,850
He didn't.

230
00:23:22,810 --> 00:23:24,250
Tanya!

231
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:28,290
Tanya...

232
00:23:37,170 --> 00:23:39,000
I told you, he's a goner.

233
00:23:47,530 --> 00:23:49,250
I'm watching you, bitch.

234
00:24:07,010 --> 00:24:08,770
Why didn't you run away?

235
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:13,410
Give me your hands.

236
00:24:31,130 --> 00:24:33,250
What's this concerning,
Comrade Captain?

237
00:24:33,770 --> 00:24:37,560
I need to file a report.
Absence without leave.

238
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:43,010
Don't report the sergeant. They'll
hold you responsible for the money.

239
00:24:45,410 --> 00:24:47,290
They'll fuck you up, for sure.

240
00:24:47,490 --> 00:24:49,960
I never touched the money,
and I'm still getting screwed.

241
00:24:52,930 --> 00:24:56,400
